HEADWORD: Mercer
<hw>Mer"cer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>mercier</ets>, fr. L. <ets>merx</ets>, <ets>mercis</ets>, wares,
merchandise. See <er>Merchant</er>.]</ety> <def>Originally, a dealer in
any kind of goods or wares; now restricted to a dealer in textile
fabrics, as silks or woolens.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mercerize</ent>⟦br⟧
